<section id="ss_jslee_interop">
  <title>JRuby/Rails Integration with Torquebox Telco Framework</title>

  <para>Mobicents Sip Servlets is now featuring, through the <ulink
  url="http://torquebox.org/">Torquebox</ulink> Telco Framework, JRuby on
  Rails integration so that you create powerful pure or converged VoIP JRuby
  on Rails applications. </para>

  <para>The pros of using JRuby is that you can use a powerful and well
  deployed scripting language that allow you to modify your application at
  runtime (this is true even for the SIP and Media part that Mobicents Sip
  Servlets offer) without restarting the server allowing for greater
  productivity. In addition, TorqueBox is a new kind of Ruby application
  platform that integrates popular technologies such as Ruby-on-Rails, while
  extending the footprint of Ruby applications to include support for Job
  Scheduling, Task Queues, SOAP Handling, ... </para>

  <para>To get more information on how to build pure JRuby-Rails applications
  leveraging Mobicents Sip Servlets to handle SIP and Media please checkout
  the <ulink
  url="http://torquebox.org/documentation/browse/LATEST/telecom.html">Torquebox
  documentation</ulink></para>

  <para>Check this <ulink
  url="http://jeanderuelle.blogspot.com/2009/03/my-jruby-rails-app-on-jboss-can-make.html">blog
  post</ulink> to help you create your first pure Torquebox JRuby Telco
  application and our pure JRuby on Rails Telco example showcasing this
  integration.</para>
</section>
